<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <head>
    <title>CSS Writing Modes Test: vertical alignment - 'sub' property (central baseline with vertical-lr)</title>
    <link rel="author" title="Hajime Shiozawa" href="mailto:hajime.shiozawa@gmail.com" />
    <link rel="help" title="4.4. Baseline Alignment" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-writing-modes/#baseline-alignment" />
    <meta name="assert" content="This test checks the generation of text baseline with vertical align property. When 'writing-mode' is vertical and when 'text-orientation' is 'mixed' or 'upright', then the central baseline is used as the dominant baseline." />
    <meta name="flags" content="ahem image" />
    <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
      div > p {
        font: 40px/1 "Ahem";
        background-color: orange;
      }

      /* vertical-align */
      img {
        vertical-align: sub;
      }
      img.box {
        margin-top: -50px;
      }
      img.line {
        margin-top: -210px;
      }

      /* writing-mode property */
      .vertical-lr {
        writing-mode: vertical-lr;
        -webkit-writing-mode: vertical-lr;
      }

      /* text-orientation property */
      .mixed {
        text-orientation: mixed;
        -webkit-text-orientation: mixed;
      }
      .upright {
        text-orientation: upright;
        -webkit-text-orientation: upright;
      }

      /* font-size */
      .half {
        vertical-align: text-top;
        font-size: 0.5em;
      }
  ]]></style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Test passes if the <strong>right side</strong> edge of black block is touching a thin blue line
      and if the center of yellow box (showed as blue line) is aligned to a thin blue line in each 2 orange rectangles
      and if all 2 orange rectangles are <strong>identical</strong>.</p>

    <div class="vertical-lr">
      <p class="mixed"><span><sub><span class="half">LLLLLLLLLL</span></sub>
        <img class="line" src="./support/blue-vert-line_1x220.png" alt="Image download support must be enabled" />
        <img class="box" src="./support/vert-box_59x59.png" alt="Image download support must be enabled" /></span>
      </p>
      <p class="upright"><span><sub><span class="half">LLLLLLLLLL</span></sub>
        <img class="line" src="./support/blue-vert-line_1x220.png" alt="Image download support must be enabled" />
        <img class="box" src="./support/vert-box_59x59.png" alt="Image download support must be enabled" /></span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
